# Student Employment Opportunities

## Gain Experience, Earn Money

New York Tech offers a variety of employment opportunities that allow students to gain professional experience while earning income. Positions are available through Federal Work-Study (FWS), Student Aid, Veterans Work-Study, and Graduate Assistantship programs. Employment opportunities are available throughout the academic year and summer.

## Eligibility Requirements

To work as a student employee, you must:

* Be currently enrolled in classes.
* Remain in good academic and disciplinary standing.
* Not work on campus after graduation unless continuing into the next degree level at New York Tech.
* Work a maximum of:

  * **20 hours per week** during the academic year.
  * **35 hours per week** during summer and academic breaks.

## Federal Work-Study (FWS)

The Federal Work-Study Program provides eligible students with part-time employment opportunities funded by the U.S. government. Students earn hourly wages while working in on-campus or approved off-campus positions.

### Benefits

* Earn money to help offset educational expenses.
* Gain valuable professional experience.
* Build skills and strengthen your résumé.
* Network with faculty, staff, and community organizations.

### Community Service Opportunities

Students awarded Federal Work-Study funding may also work with approved nonprofit organizations through the Community Service Program. These positions provide meaningful service experiences while developing professional skills and community connections.

## Veterans Work-Study

The Veterans Affairs (VA) Work-Study Program provides additional financial support to eligible student veterans who assist with VA-related services on campus or at approved off-campus locations.

### Eligibility

Students must:

* Be enrolled at least three-quarters time.
* Use an approved VA education benefits program.
* Secure an approved VA-related work-study position.
* Complete the work-study contract while remaining eligible for VA benefits.

## Student Aid Positions

Student Aid positions are funded directly by New York Tech and are available to matriculated students regardless of their financial aid package.

### Benefits

* Flexible on-campus employment.
* Hourly compensation.
* Professional development and workplace experience.

## Graduate Assistantships

Graduate Assistantships provide qualified graduate students with opportunities to contribute to academic and administrative activities while receiving partial or full tuition remission.

### Responsibilities May Include

* Assisting faculty in classrooms, laboratories, or studios.
* Supporting academic research projects.
* Providing administrative support to departments and campus facilities.

Tuition remission is awarded based on the number of hours worked and the requirements of the specific assistantship position.

## Opportunities for International Students

International students are eligible to apply for both Student Aid positions and Graduate Assistantships.

* **Student Aid Positions:** Hourly paid employment opportunities.
* **Graduate Assistantships:** Tuition remission awarded in exchange for service hours completed during the semester.

These programs provide valuable professional experience, campus engagement opportunities, and financial support while pursuing a degree at New York Tech.

